  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Deployed in operating-theatre environments where temperature drift (18–26 °C), ambient pressure variation (sea-level to 2 500 m altitude), and electromagnetic interference from adjacent surgical equipment are all plausible. Validation was conducted exclusively under controlled laboratory conditions at 22 °C and atmospheric pressure; no environmental-sensitivity study has been linked and the operating envelope does not bound these parameters.",
